ROTTERDAM - Roger Federer moved to within two victories of becoming the oldest world number one of all time on Wednesday when he eased past Belgium's Ruben Bemelmans 6-1, 6-2 at the Rotterdam ATP event. .@rogerfederer is now two matches from the No. 1 ranking after sprinting past Bemelmans 6-1, 6-2 in just 47 minutes in R1 of Rotterdam!https://t.co/ke9iGbd1Si #USOpen pic.twitter.com/ik6oDY3O7x The 36-year-old needed just over 45 minutes to clinch victory and next faces Germany's Philipp Kohlschreiber in the second round on Thursday. Roger Federer’s Valentine’s Day gift to you: pic.twitter.com/fI1LaAftMO If Federer reaches the semi-finals, he will depose Rafael Nadal on top of the rankings and become the oldest world number one. AFP